                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10053: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-06-10T13:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 10, 1928—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 10—11 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>444. My telegram No. 442, June 9, 11 [<hi rend="italic">7</hi>] p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Committee of Safety wound up its affairs today, announcing as its reason
                        that Yen Hsi-shan has been appointed by Nationalist Government as commander
                        in chief of Peking-Tientsin area and has deputed representatives “To come to
                        Peking and consult regarding the taking over of affairs.” This abrupt
                        relinquishment of responsibilities by the committee is understood to have
                        been induced by apprehensions resulting from violation by Kuominchun of safe
                        conduct promised by the Nationalist Government to General Pao and his
                        protective forces.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Kuominchun forces are now southeast and north of Peking and there is
                        increasing disposition among both Chinese and foreigners to believe that
                        Feng is preparing to force Yen out and assume control.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
